cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with scene labeling, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a novel method for learning better deep feature representations using semantic context guided supervision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces novel training strategies and network structures, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper utilizes semantic context to create label hierarchies, which involves some level of natural language processing, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with classification and prediction, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on four popular datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
